						               													<description>In Thailand, There is an attempt to create boardgames that use the Thai alphabet in a Scrabble like game and its name is Kham Khom (&amp;#224;&amp;#184;&amp;#132;&amp;#224;&amp;#184;&amp;#179;&amp;#224;&amp;#184;&amp;#132;&amp;#224;&amp;#184;&amp;#161; - meaning: epigram)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Instead of using 26 English - Latin letters, the game uses the Thai alphabet. The Thai alphabet has 44 consonants , 20 vowels, 4 Diacritics and some symbols that are necessary in usage. The game uses only 42 consonants   (At   present, 2 of the 44 are dropped from being used) and drawn vowel tiles    can be set aside and then can be played anytime in the turn without drawing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules of Kham Khom is some slightly different from Scrabble because the Thai alphabet has a more complex system than the English - Latin alphabet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
